The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 Spate of student deaths on street

 Hyderabad: The streets of Secunderabad have turned into danger zones for students, with four lives being cut short and an engineering student losing his leg since Saturday, reports our special correspondent.

 Among the casualties is four-year-old Rithika of St Anns School of Secunderabad. The nursery student was mowed down by a DCM Toyota on Thursday. On Monday, a military truck ran over a 17-year-old student of St Anns College. The next day, a seven-year-old girl was killed on the spot after being run over by an autorickshaw while she was waiting at a bus stand. The same day, a student of Villa Marie School was crushed under a bus.

 A 19-year-old student of Muffakam Jha Engineering College lost his leg on Monday as he was allegedly pushed out of a local train while travelling to the institute.

 It is a case of social callousness in the administration, said C.V. Rao, the principal of Villa Marie School. 

 CBI kickstarts Centaur probe

 New Delhi: After spotting irregularities in official papers, the CBI has kicked off its probe into the sale of two Centaur hotels in 2002, when Arun Shourie was divestment minister in the Vajpayee government, reports our special correspondent.

 The agency has registered two preliminary enquiries (PEs) ? one over Centaur Juhu and the other over Airport Centaur ? after going through documents provided by the finance ministrys department of divestment.

 Both PEs have been registered against unknown public servants of the ministries of divestment and civil aviation, Air-India and the Hotel Corporation of India (HCI), an Air-India subsidiary which owned the hotels, sources said.

 If we get enough incriminating material during the PE, we will register a proper case and would call the then officials of the various departments and ministries for interrogation, an agency source said.

 Temple arrest

 Jammu (PTI): Security forces have arrested a Jaish-e-Mohammad militant, wanted in connection with last months terrorist attack in Ayodhya, from Poonch district.

 Rafeeq alias Lassa was picked up on Thursday during a raid on a hideout in Mendhar tehsil of the district. Some explosives were recovered from him.

 Air force fill-up

 Jammu (PTI): Air Marshal Ajit Bhavnani, the head of the Strategic Forces Command that is the custodian of nuclear weapons, has been asked to take over the responsibilities of the vice-chief of the air force on an ad hoc basis. 

 Cola notice

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has issued a notice to soft drink major Coca-Cola on an application seeking a stay on a Kerala High Court order allowing the companys Plachimada-based bottling unit to draw five lakh litres of ground water a day. 

 A textile showroom in Tamil Nadus Tirunelveli has made it to the Guinness World Records for producing the longest sari in the world. It measures 1,276 feet and weighs 40 kg.




